WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:18.360
Alice's Adventures in Wonderland by Lewis Carroll

00:18.360 --> 00:32.040
Copyright Blackcat Publishing

00:32.040 --> 00:36.920
Chapter 1 The White Rabbit

00:36.920 --> 00:39.120
It is a sunny afternoon.

00:39.120 --> 00:42.440
Alice and her sister are sitting by the river.

00:42.440 --> 00:47.320
Alice's sister is reading a book with no pictures.

00:47.320 --> 00:52.200
'I don't like books without any pictures.' Alice thinks.
  
00:52.200 --> 00:54.040
She is sleepy.

00:54.040 --> 00:57.160
Just then she sees a white rabbit.

00:57.160 --> 01:01.760
He looks at his watch and says, 'I'm late.'
  
01:01.760 --> 01:05.160
'How strange!' Alice thinks.

01:05.160 --> 01:08.120
'A rabbit with a watch!'

01:08.120 --> 01:12.880
She follows the rabbit across the grass and into a big hole.

01:12.880 --> 01:16.000
She falls slowly down the hole.

01:16.000 --> 01:19.640
Then she stops falling and stands up.

01:19.640 --> 01:21.720
She looks around.

01:21.720 --> 01:26.200
Alice sees the rabbit again and follows him.

01:26.200 --> 01:30.360
He is running around a hall with a lot of doors.

01:30.360 --> 01:35.240
Then she sees a glass table with a small key on it.

01:35.240 --> 01:40.800
She takes the key and tries to open the doors, but she can't.

01:40.800 --> 01:45.600
Then she sees a very small door and opens it.

01:45.600 --> 01:48.480
There is a beautiful garden.

01:48.480 --> 01:51.240
I want to go into that garden.

01:51.240 --> 01:52.240
thinks Alice.

01:52.240 --> 01:55.400
But I'm too big.

01:55.400 --> 02:00.120
She puts the key on the glass table and sees a bottle on it.

02:00.120 --> 02:03.800
It says, drink me on the bottle.

02:03.800 --> 02:07.560
She takes the bottle and drinks it all.

02:07.560 --> 02:10.560
Oh, how strange.

02:10.560 --> 02:15.560
She says, now I'm very small and I can go into the garden.

02:16.560 --> 02:21.000
But the door is closed and the key is on the table.

02:21.000 --> 02:25.360
She is too small now and she can't get the key.

02:25.360 --> 02:29.760
She is very sad and starts to cry.

02:29.760 --> 02:34.160
Alice sees a small glass box under the table.

02:34.160 --> 02:40.040
Inside the box there is a cake with the words, eat me on it.

02:40.040 --> 02:43.640
I'm going to eat it, says Alice.

02:43.880 --> 02:48.160
Perhaps I can grow and take the key from the table.

02:48.160 --> 02:51.800
She eats the cake, but nothing happens.

02:51.800 --> 02:54.520
Then suddenly she becomes big.

02:54.520 --> 02:58.000
Now I can get the key.

02:58.000 --> 02:59.800
She thinks.

02:59.800 --> 03:03.920
She takes the key and goes to the door to the garden.

03:03.920 --> 03:07.800
But she is too big and can't go in.

03:07.800 --> 03:11.520
She sits down and starts to cry again.

03:11.520 --> 03:14.520
Her tears make a big pool.

03:14.520 --> 03:18.160
Suddenly she sees the white rabbit again.

03:18.160 --> 03:24.240
He is wearing a lovely jacket and he has got white gloves in one hand and flowers in the

03:24.240 --> 03:25.240
other.

03:25.240 --> 03:30.320
Oh, the Duchess is going to be angry because I'm late.

03:30.320 --> 03:32.320
Says the white rabbit.

03:32.320 --> 03:34.560
Excuse me, sir.

03:34.560 --> 03:36.040
Says Alice.

03:36.040 --> 03:39.680
The white rabbit is afraid and runs away.

03:39.680 --> 03:43.200
His white gloves fall to the floor.

03:43.200 --> 03:49.200
Alice looks at her hand and she is suddenly wearing one of the white rabbit's gloves.

03:49.200 --> 03:51.520
Oh, no.

03:51.520 --> 03:55.360
She says, I'm becoming small again.

03:55.360 --> 03:58.000
What's happening to me?

03:58.000 --> 04:03.240
Alice is small again and she suddenly falls into a pool of water.

04:03.240 --> 04:05.840
I'm in the sea.

04:05.840 --> 04:07.160
She thinks.

04:07.160 --> 04:09.160
But it is not the sea.

04:09.160 --> 04:12.280
It is the pool of Alice's tears.

04:12.280 --> 04:14.960
She sees a mouse swimming near her.

04:14.960 --> 04:16.960
Hello, Mouse.

04:16.960 --> 04:17.960
Says Alice.

04:17.960 --> 04:19.960
I'm tired.

04:19.960 --> 04:22.960
I want to get out of this pool.

04:22.960 --> 04:25.960
The mouse does not answer.

04:25.960 --> 04:29.120
Perhaps it doesn't understand English.

04:29.120 --> 04:31.120
Alice thinks.

04:31.120 --> 04:33.080
Maybe it understands French.

04:33.080 --> 04:37.080
Ooh, a machete.

04:37.080 --> 04:38.680
Says Alice.

04:38.680 --> 04:42.080
This is the first sentence in her French book.

04:42.080 --> 04:47.440
The mouse is angry and says in English, I don't like cats.

04:47.440 --> 04:50.280
My family doesn't like cats.

04:50.280 --> 04:52.240
I'm a mouse.

04:52.240 --> 05:00.400
He swims away and Alice follows him.

05:00.400 --> 05:01.400
Chapter 2.

05:01.400 --> 05:03.560
The blue caterpillar.

05:04.560 --> 05:08.960
Soon, there are other strange animals in the pool.

05:08.960 --> 05:14.360
A duck, a dodo, a parrot and a baby eagle.

05:14.360 --> 05:19.360
Alice gets out of the pool and the animals follow her.

05:19.360 --> 05:21.360
We're all wet.

05:21.360 --> 05:22.960
Says the dodo.

05:22.960 --> 05:25.960
Let's run a race and get dry.

05:25.960 --> 05:27.960
That's a good idea.

05:27.960 --> 05:29.760
Says the parrot.

05:29.960 --> 05:34.360
Alice and the animals run a race and they get dry.

05:34.360 --> 05:36.960
After the race, the duck asks.

05:36.960 --> 05:39.760
Who wins this race?

05:39.760 --> 05:44.160
Everyone wins and everyone gets a prize.

05:44.160 --> 05:45.560
Says the dodo.

05:45.560 --> 05:49.960
And Alice is giving the prizes.

05:49.960 --> 05:52.360
But I haven't got any prizes.

05:52.360 --> 05:56.960
Alice thinks Alice does not know what to do.

05:56.960 --> 06:01.760
She puts her hand in her pocket and finds a box of sweets.

06:01.760 --> 06:04.360
Here are some sweets for everyone.

06:04.360 --> 06:08.760
She says she gives one sweet to every animal.

06:08.760 --> 06:11.160
Alice must have a prize too.

06:11.160 --> 06:12.560
Says the mouse.

06:12.560 --> 06:14.160
Of course.

06:14.160 --> 06:15.760
The dodo says.

06:15.760 --> 06:18.960
What have you got for a prize, Alice?

06:18.960 --> 06:21.160
I've only got this box.

06:21.160 --> 06:25.760
Says Alice and she gives him the empty sweet box.

06:25.760 --> 06:26.560
Good.

06:26.560 --> 06:27.960
Says the dodo.

06:27.960 --> 06:30.360
Here's your prize, Alice.

06:30.360 --> 06:33.360
A beautiful box.

06:33.360 --> 06:35.160
How strange.

06:35.160 --> 06:36.760
She thinks.

06:36.760 --> 06:41.360
She looks at the dodo and says, thank you.

06:41.360 --> 06:45.160
The animals go away and Alice is alone.

06:45.160 --> 06:49.160
She hears a noise and sees the white rabbit.

06:49.160 --> 06:50.960
The Duchess.

06:50.960 --> 06:52.760
Says the white rabbit.

06:52.760 --> 06:55.560
She's going to be angry.

06:55.560 --> 06:57.960
Where are my gloves?

06:57.960 --> 06:59.960
Alice looks around.

06:59.960 --> 07:04.760
Suddenly everything is different and she is in the countryside.

07:04.760 --> 07:08.160
The white rabbit sees Alice and says.

07:08.160 --> 07:11.160
What are you doing here, Mary Ann?

07:11.160 --> 07:14.960
Run home and bring me my white gloves.

07:14.960 --> 07:17.560
He thinks I'm his servant.

07:17.560 --> 07:18.960
thinks Alice.

07:18.960 --> 07:23.560
She runs to the white rabbit's house and gets his gloves.

07:23.560 --> 07:27.760
Then she sees a bottle on a table and thinks.

07:27.760 --> 07:34.160
Every time I eat or drink something here, interesting things happen.

07:34.160 --> 07:37.760
She drinks it and starts to grow.

07:37.760 --> 07:43.560
She is now very big and puts one hand out of the window of the house.

07:43.560 --> 07:46.560
Mary Ann, where are you?

07:46.560 --> 07:48.160
asks the white rabbit.

07:48.160 --> 07:50.360
Where are my gloves?

07:50.360 --> 07:53.160
He tries to open the door of his house.

07:53.160 --> 07:57.160
But he can't because Alice's arm is against it.

07:57.160 --> 08:00.160
The white rabbit calls his gardener.

08:00.160 --> 08:01.160
Pat.

08:01.160 --> 08:02.160
Pat.

08:02.160 --> 08:04.160
Where are you?

08:04.160 --> 08:06.160
I'm here, sir.

08:06.160 --> 08:07.160
Says Pat.

08:07.160 --> 08:12.160
There are other animals near the house and they want to help the white rabbit.

08:12.160 --> 08:14.160
Come and help me.

08:14.160 --> 08:17.160
Says the white rabbit angrily.

08:17.160 --> 08:20.160
What's that in the window, Pat?

08:20.160 --> 08:22.160
It's a hand.

08:22.160 --> 08:23.160
Says Pat.

08:23.160 --> 08:24.160
A hand?

08:24.160 --> 08:26.160
Says the white rabbit.

08:26.160 --> 08:28.160
What are you saying?

08:28.160 --> 08:29.160
Listen to me.

08:29.160 --> 08:32.160
We must burn the house.

08:32.160 --> 08:33.160
What?

08:33.160 --> 08:35.160
Shouts Alice.

08:35.160 --> 08:38.160
The animals are silent for a moment.

08:38.160 --> 08:41.160
Then they throw stones through the windows.

08:41.160 --> 08:44.160
The stones become little cakes.

08:44.160 --> 08:48.160
Alice eats some of them and becomes small.

08:48.160 --> 08:51.160
She is happy and runs out of the house.

08:51.160 --> 08:56.160
The animals try to catch her, but she runs away into the wood.

08:56.160 --> 09:00.160
Alice sees a big mushroom in the wood.

09:00.160 --> 09:04.160
On top of the mushroom, there is a sleepy caterpillar.

09:04.160 --> 09:07.160
He is smoking a long pipe.

09:07.160 --> 09:09.160
Who are you?

09:09.160 --> 09:11.160
He asks quietly.

09:11.160 --> 09:14.160
I... I don't know.

09:14.160 --> 09:16.160
Says Alice.

09:16.160 --> 09:19.160
My size changes all the time.

09:19.160 --> 09:21.160
Now I'm very small.

09:21.160 --> 09:24.160
I don't understand.

09:24.160 --> 09:26.160
Says the blue caterpillar.

09:26.160 --> 09:28.160
I can't explain.

09:28.160 --> 09:30.160
Says Alice.

09:30.160 --> 09:32.160
Let me give you an example.

09:32.160 --> 09:36.160
One day, you're going to become a butterfly.

09:36.160 --> 09:38.160
That's strange, isn't it?

09:38.160 --> 09:39.160
No.

09:39.160 --> 09:42.160
That's not strange at all.

09:42.160 --> 09:44.160
Says the caterpillar.

09:44.160 --> 09:47.160
But who are you?

09:47.160 --> 09:51.160
I want to know who you are first.

09:51.160 --> 09:52.160
Says Alice.

09:52.160 --> 09:53.160
Why?

09:53.160 --> 09:55.160
Ask the caterpillar.

09:55.160 --> 09:58.160
Alice can't answer the question.

09:58.160 --> 10:01.160
She is angry and walks away.

10:01.160 --> 10:03.160
Come back.

10:03.160 --> 10:04.160
Says the caterpillar.

10:04.160 --> 10:07.160
I want to tell you something.

10:07.160 --> 10:12.160
Alice goes back to the caterpillar and looks at him.

10:12.160 --> 10:16.160
You must never be angry.

10:16.160 --> 10:18.160
He says,

10:18.160 --> 10:20.160
Is that all?

10:20.160 --> 10:22.160
asks Alice angrily.

10:22.160 --> 10:23.160
No.

10:23.160 --> 10:25.160
Says the caterpillar.

10:25.160 --> 10:29.160
He smokes his pipe and then gets off the mushroom.

10:29.160 --> 10:34.160
One side of this mushroom makes you big.

10:34.160 --> 10:39.160
And the other side makes you small.

10:39.160 --> 10:42.160
Alice looks at the mushroom and thinks,

10:42.160 --> 10:47.160
What side of the mushroom have I got to eat?

10:47.160 --> 10:52.160
She takes a piece from each side and then eats the first piece.

10:52.160 --> 10:55.160
Suddenly she grows very small.

10:55.160 --> 11:00.160
She eats the other piece and her neck grows long.

11:00.160 --> 11:06.160
Then she eats another piece and she becomes the right size.

11:06.160 --> 11:11.160
She is happy.

11:11.160 --> 11:13.160
Chapter 3.

11:13.160 --> 11:16.160
The Cheshire Cat.

11:16.160 --> 11:18.160
Alice walks in the woods.

11:18.160 --> 11:22.160
She sees a nice garden and a small house.

11:22.160 --> 11:24.160
I'm too big.

11:24.160 --> 11:25.160
She thinks.

11:25.160 --> 11:28.160
I can't get into that house.

11:28.160 --> 11:32.160
I must eat a piece of mushroom and become small again.

11:32.160 --> 11:36.160
Soon she is nine inches tall.

11:36.160 --> 11:41.160
Suddenly a servant comes out of the wood and goes to the small house.

11:41.160 --> 11:44.160
His face is like a fish.

11:44.160 --> 11:49.160
Another servant opens the door and his face is like a frog.

11:49.160 --> 11:55.160
The fish servant has got a big letter in his hand and says,

11:55.160 --> 11:58.160
For the Duchess.

11:58.160 --> 12:04.160
An invitation from the Queen to play croquet.

12:04.160 --> 12:06.160
The frog servant says,

12:06.160 --> 12:09.160
From the Queen.

12:09.160 --> 12:14.160
An invitation for the Duchess to play croquet.

12:14.160 --> 12:18.160
What strange servants!

12:18.160 --> 12:20.160
Says Alice, laughing.

12:20.160 --> 12:24.160
Alice goes to the house and says,

12:24.160 --> 12:26.160
Can I come in?

12:26.160 --> 12:30.160
Just open the door and go in.

12:30.160 --> 12:32.160
Says the servant.

12:32.160 --> 12:34.160
Then she sees the Duchess.

12:34.160 --> 12:39.160
She is sitting on a small chair with a baby in her arms.

12:39.160 --> 12:41.160
There is a cook in the kitchen.

12:41.160 --> 12:43.160
She is making some soup.

12:43.160 --> 12:46.160
There is too much pepper in the soup.

12:46.160 --> 12:49.160
Alice thinks and she sneezes.

12:49.160 --> 12:50.160
Achoo!

12:50.160 --> 12:53.160
Then the Duchess sneezes.

12:53.160 --> 12:55.160
Achoo!

12:55.160 --> 12:57.160
And the baby sneezes.

12:57.160 --> 12:59.160
Achoo!

12:59.160 --> 13:03.160
But the cook and a big cat do not sneeze.

13:03.160 --> 13:07.160
The cat sits near the cook and smiles.

13:07.160 --> 13:10.160
Alice asks the Duchess.

13:10.160 --> 13:13.160
Why does your cat smile?

13:13.160 --> 13:16.160
Because it's a Cheshire cat.

13:16.160 --> 13:18.160
Says the Duchess.

13:18.160 --> 13:22.160
All Cheshire cats smile, don't you know?

13:22.160 --> 13:24.160
No I don't.

13:24.160 --> 13:25.160
Says Alice.

13:25.160 --> 13:28.160
You don't know much.

13:28.160 --> 13:30.160
Says the Duchess.

13:30.160 --> 13:37.160
Suddenly the cook starts throwing plates, cups and pots at the Duchess and the baby.

13:37.160 --> 13:40.160
There is a terrible noise and Alice is afraid.

13:40.160 --> 13:42.160
Oh please be careful.

13:42.160 --> 13:44.160
Says Alice.

13:44.160 --> 13:46.160
The poor baby.

13:46.160 --> 13:48.160
Don't think about the baby.

13:48.160 --> 13:50.160
Says the Duchess.

13:50.160 --> 13:52.160
It's mine.

13:52.160 --> 13:55.160
She starts singing to the baby.

13:55.160 --> 13:58.160
But suddenly she throws it to Alice.

13:58.160 --> 13:59.160
Here.

13:59.160 --> 14:01.160
Take the baby.

14:01.160 --> 14:07.160
She says, I must go and play croquet with the Queen.

14:07.160 --> 14:09.160
She runs out of the house.

14:09.160 --> 14:14.160
The cook throws a plate at her but it does not hit her.

14:14.160 --> 14:17.160
Alice goes outside with a baby.

14:17.160 --> 14:19.160
It makes strange noises.

14:19.160 --> 14:22.160
Alice looks at it carefully.

14:22.160 --> 14:25.160
It is a baby pig.

14:25.160 --> 14:26.160
A pig?

14:26.160 --> 14:29.160
Says Alice, surprised.

14:29.160 --> 14:34.160
She puts it down immediately and it runs into the wood.

14:34.160 --> 14:38.160
Just then Alice sees the Cheshire cat in a tree.

14:38.160 --> 14:41.160
It looks at Alice and smiles.

14:41.160 --> 14:43.160
Hello Cheshire cat.

14:43.160 --> 14:45.160
Says Alice.

14:45.160 --> 14:47.160
Where can I go now?

14:47.160 --> 14:51.160
Well, where do you want to go?

14:51.160 --> 14:53.160
Asks the Cheshire cat.

14:53.160 --> 14:56.160
I, I don't know.

14:56.160 --> 14:57.160
Says Alice.

14:57.160 --> 15:02.160
You can go that way on the right and you can visit the hatter.

15:02.160 --> 15:04.160
Says the Cheshire cat.

15:04.160 --> 15:10.160
Or you can go that way on the left and you can visit the March Hare.

15:10.160 --> 15:11.160
It doesn't matter.

15:11.160 --> 15:13.160
They're both mad.

15:13.160 --> 15:15.160
Oh dear.

15:15.160 --> 15:16.160
Says Alice.

15:16.160 --> 15:19.160
I don't want to visit mad people.

15:19.160 --> 15:22.160
Then you're in the wrong place.

15:22.160 --> 15:24.160
Says the Cheshire cat.

15:24.160 --> 15:26.160
We're all mad here.

15:26.160 --> 15:28.160
You're mad too.

15:28.160 --> 15:30.160
How do you know I'm mad?

15:30.160 --> 15:31.160
Asks Alice.

15:31.160 --> 15:32.160
You're here.

15:32.160 --> 15:34.160
Says the Cheshire cat.

15:34.160 --> 15:37.160
So of course you're mad.

15:37.160 --> 15:41.160
Are you going to play croquet with the Queen today?

15:41.160 --> 15:43.160
Asks the Cheshire cat.

15:43.160 --> 15:44.160
No.

15:44.160 --> 15:46.160
I haven't got an invitation.

15:46.160 --> 15:47.160
Says Alice.

15:47.160 --> 15:49.160
I'm going to be there.

15:49.160 --> 15:51.160
Says the Cheshire cat.

15:51.160 --> 15:54.160
And he suddenly goes away.

15:54.160 --> 15:57.160
Then he comes back and asks.

15:57.160 --> 15:59.160
Where's the baby?

15:59.160 --> 16:01.160
It's not a baby.

16:01.160 --> 16:02.160
Says Alice.

16:02.160 --> 16:03.160
It's a pig.

16:03.160 --> 16:04.160
Oh.

16:04.160 --> 16:08.160
He says and goes away again.

16:08.160 --> 16:12.160
Alice goes to the March Hare's house.

16:13.160 --> 16:15.160
What a big house.

16:15.160 --> 16:16.160
Alice thinks.

16:16.160 --> 16:19.160
But I'm very small.

16:19.160 --> 16:28.160
She eats another piece of mushroom and she becomes big.

16:28.160 --> 16:29.160
Chapter 4.

16:29.160 --> 16:32.160
The Tea Party.

16:32.160 --> 16:35.160
There is a big table in front of the house.

16:35.160 --> 16:39.160
The March Hare and the Hatter are having tea.

16:39.160 --> 16:42.160
The doormouse is on the table between them.

16:42.160 --> 16:46.160
When the March Hare and the Hatter see Alice, they say.

16:46.160 --> 16:47.160
There's no room.

16:47.160 --> 16:48.160
No room.

16:48.160 --> 16:51.160
But there's a lot of room.

16:51.160 --> 16:52.160
Says Alice.

16:52.160 --> 16:55.160
And she sits in a big chair.

16:55.160 --> 16:58.160
The Hatter looks at his watch and asks.

16:58.160 --> 17:00.160
What day is it?

17:00.160 --> 17:02.160
I think it's Monday.

17:02.160 --> 17:03.160
Says Alice.

17:03.160 --> 17:05.160
My watch says Wednesday.

17:05.160 --> 17:07.160
Says the Hatter.

17:07.160 --> 17:10.160
The March Hare puts his watch in his tea.

17:10.160 --> 17:12.160
Alice is surprised.

17:12.160 --> 17:14.160
What's he doing?

17:14.160 --> 17:16.160
She thinks.

17:16.160 --> 17:20.160
Then the March Hare takes it out and looks at it.

17:20.160 --> 17:24.160
Alice looks at the March Hare's watch and says.

17:24.160 --> 17:26.160
What a strange watch.

17:26.160 --> 17:28.160
It shows the day of the month.

17:28.160 --> 17:31.160
But it doesn't show the time.

17:31.160 --> 17:34.160
Does your watch show the year?

17:34.160 --> 17:35.160
Asks the Hatter.

17:35.160 --> 17:37.160
Of course not.

17:37.160 --> 17:38.160
Says Alice.

17:38.160 --> 17:42.160
Because it's the same year for a long time.

17:42.160 --> 17:45.160
Well, it's the same with my watch.

17:45.160 --> 17:46.160
Says the Hatter.

17:46.160 --> 17:49.160
It's always six o'clock here.

17:49.160 --> 17:51.160
Have some more tea.

17:51.160 --> 17:53.160
Says the March Hare.

17:53.160 --> 17:54.160
Thank you.

17:54.160 --> 17:56.160
But I haven't got any tea.

17:56.160 --> 17:57.160
Says Alice.

17:57.160 --> 17:59.160
How can I have more?

17:59.160 --> 18:00.160
Oh.

18:00.160 --> 18:02.160
Says the Hatter.

18:02.160 --> 18:05.160
You can always have more than nothing.

18:05.160 --> 18:08.160
Alice is confused and angry.

18:08.160 --> 18:12.160
She gets up from the table and walks away through the trees.

18:12.160 --> 18:17.160
The Hatter tries to put the door mouse into the teapot.

18:17.160 --> 18:20.160
What a stupid tea party.

18:20.160 --> 18:21.160
She thinks.

18:21.160 --> 18:26.160
Alice is walking in the wood and sees a door in a tree.

18:26.160 --> 18:31.160
She opens it and sees the hall with a glass table again.

18:31.160 --> 18:35.160
This time I want to go into the garden.

18:35.160 --> 18:36.160
She thinks.

18:36.160 --> 18:40.160
She takes the key and opens the door.

18:40.160 --> 18:44.160
She eats a piece of mushroom and becomes small.

18:44.160 --> 18:50.160
Then she walks into the beautiful garden with lovely flowers and fountains.

18:50.160 --> 18:56.160
There is a big rose tree near the door of the garden and she sees three gardeners.

18:56.160 --> 18:58.160
But they are not men.

18:58.160 --> 19:04.160
They are playing cards and each of them has got a head, hands and feet.

19:04.160 --> 19:07.160
They are painting the white roses red.

19:07.160 --> 19:10.160
Alice sees them and says, Hello.

19:10.160 --> 19:12.160
My name is Alice.

19:12.160 --> 19:16.160
Why are you painting the roses red?

19:16.160 --> 19:19.160
The Queen hates white roses.

19:19.160 --> 19:20.160
Says five.

19:20.160 --> 19:22.160
She only likes red roses.

19:22.160 --> 19:24.160
Says seven.

19:24.160 --> 19:29.160
We must paint them red or she's going to cut off our heads.

19:29.160 --> 19:30.160
Says two.

19:30.160 --> 19:33.160
Cut off your heads.

19:33.160 --> 19:36.160
Says Alice, surprised.

19:36.160 --> 19:43.160
Suddenly one of the cards says, Look, it's the Queen, the Queen.

19:43.160 --> 19:47.160
Alice turns around and sees a lot of people.

19:47.160 --> 19:52.160
They are all playing cards, each with a head, hands and feet.

19:52.160 --> 20:01.160
There are soldiers with clubs, servants with diamonds and spades, children with hearts and kings and queens.

20:05.160 --> 20:08.160
A drink called tea.

20:08.160 --> 20:10.160
What is tea?

20:10.160 --> 20:16.160
Tea comes from the dry leaves of the Camellia Synensis plant.

20:16.160 --> 20:21.160
This plant grows in high places with hot weather and a lot of rain.

20:21.160 --> 20:28.160
There are three types of tea, black, green and oolong.

20:28.160 --> 20:31.160
Where does tea come from?

20:31.160 --> 20:36.160
Most tea comes from India, China and Sri Lanka.

20:36.160 --> 20:44.160
But some comes from Africa, Malaysia, Indonesia, Japan and South America.

20:44.160 --> 20:48.160
Today tea grows in about 40 countries.

20:48.160 --> 20:53.160
Look at the map and find the countries.

20:53.160 --> 20:56.160
Tea around the world.

20:56.160 --> 20:59.160
The British like drinking tea.

20:59.160 --> 21:04.160
In the afternoon they sometimes have cakes and sandwiches with it.

21:04.160 --> 21:13.160
This is called afternoon tea and it means both the drink and the food, like in the picture on page 38.

21:14.160 --> 21:20.160
Some big hotels have got tea rooms where people go to talk and enjoy a cup of tea.

21:20.160 --> 21:25.160
You can also get afternoon tea in most cafes.

21:25.160 --> 21:30.160
The Japanese have a tea ceremony called Cha Noyu.

21:30.160 --> 21:34.160
They drink their tea in a special tea house.

21:34.160 --> 21:37.160
Everything is important in this ceremony.

21:37.160 --> 21:43.160
The tea, the teapot, the cups and the teaspoons.

21:43.160 --> 21:51.160
In North Africa and the Middle East people drink strong hot tea in small glasses with sugar.

21:51.160 --> 21:56.160
In some countries of North Africa people drink green tea and mint.

21:56.160 --> 22:00.160
It is a good drink in hot weather.

22:00.160 --> 22:05.160
In Turkey people drink tea in special glasses with cubes of sugar.

22:05.160 --> 22:11.160
They drink more tea in Turkey than in any other country.

22:11.160 --> 22:15.160
Russian people use a samovar to make tea.

22:15.160 --> 22:23.160
A samovar has got a lot of hot water so the Russians can drink tea all day.

22:23.160 --> 22:29.160
You can drink tea hot or cold with milk or with lemon.

22:29.160 --> 22:36.160
A lot of doctors say tea is good for you.

22:36.160 --> 22:41.160
Chapter 5, Croquet

22:41.160 --> 22:45.160
The Queen stops and looks at Alice.

22:45.160 --> 22:48.160
What's your name, child?

22:48.160 --> 22:50.160
asks the Queen.

22:50.160 --> 22:53.160
My name's Alice, she says.

22:53.160 --> 22:58.160
Then she thinks, I mustn't be afraid. They're only cards.

22:58.160 --> 23:02.160
The Queen looks at the gardeners and asks,

23:02.160 --> 23:06.160
And who are they?

23:06.160 --> 23:08.160
Don't ask me, says Alice.

23:08.160 --> 23:10.160
I don't know.

23:10.160 --> 23:15.160
The Queen is very angry with Alice and says,

23:15.160 --> 23:18.160
Cut off her head!

23:18.160 --> 23:21.160
The King looks at the Queen and says,

23:21.160 --> 23:24.160
But she's only a child, dear.

23:24.160 --> 23:28.160
The Queen is now angry with the gardeners.

23:28.160 --> 23:31.160
Cut off their heads!

23:31.160 --> 23:35.160
She says to the soldiers, the gardeners are afraid.

23:35.160 --> 23:38.160
Alice, Alice!

23:38.160 --> 23:40.160
They shout.

23:40.160 --> 23:42.160
Please help us.

23:42.160 --> 23:46.160
Come here fast, says Alice.

23:46.160 --> 23:50.160
She puts them in a flower pot and no one can see them.

23:50.160 --> 23:53.160
Are their heads off?

23:53.160 --> 23:55.160
asks the Queen.

23:55.160 --> 23:59.160
The soldiers can't see the cards.

23:59.160 --> 24:02.160
Their heads are gone.

24:02.160 --> 24:04.160
Say the soldiers.

24:04.160 --> 24:07.160
That's good, says the Queen.

24:07.160 --> 24:10.160
Now let's play Croquet.

24:10.160 --> 24:13.160
Can you play Croquet, dear?

24:13.160 --> 24:16.160
Yes, says Alice.

24:16.160 --> 24:18.160
Come on then!

24:18.160 --> 24:19.160
Says the Queen.

24:19.160 --> 24:24.160
Alice walks away with the Queen, the King and the others.

24:24.160 --> 24:27.160
Go to your places!

24:27.160 --> 24:29.160
Shouts the Queen.

24:29.160 --> 24:32.160
Let's start the game!

24:32.160 --> 24:34.160
What a funny game!

24:34.160 --> 24:36.160
Alice thinks.

24:36.160 --> 24:40.160
The balls are hedgehogs and the mallets are flamingos.

24:40.160 --> 24:43.160
It's going to be difficult.

24:43.160 --> 24:47.160
During the game, the Queen is often angry and shouts,

24:47.160 --> 24:49.160
Cut off his head!

24:49.160 --> 24:51.160
Cut off her head!

24:51.160 --> 24:53.160
Oh dear.

24:53.160 --> 24:54.160
Alice thinks.

24:54.160 --> 24:57.160
What's going to happen to my head?

24:57.160 --> 25:01.160
Suddenly Alice sees the Cheshire Cat.

25:01.160 --> 25:03.160
She is happy to see him.

25:03.160 --> 25:05.160
How are you, dear?

25:05.160 --> 25:07.160
asks the Cheshire Cat.

25:07.160 --> 25:09.160
I don't like this game.

25:09.160 --> 25:11.160
Says Alice.

25:11.160 --> 25:15.160
No one knows how to play and everyone is angry.

25:15.160 --> 25:17.160
Do you like the Queen?

25:17.160 --> 25:19.160
asks the Cheshire Cat.

25:19.160 --> 25:21.160
No, I don't.

25:21.160 --> 25:22.160
Says Alice.

25:22.160 --> 25:25.160
The King sees Alice and the Cheshire Cat.

25:25.160 --> 25:28.160
Who are you talking to?

25:28.160 --> 25:29.160
He asks.

25:29.160 --> 25:32.160
It's my friend, the Cheshire Cat.

25:32.160 --> 25:34.160
Says Alice.

25:34.160 --> 25:36.160
I don't like it.

25:36.160 --> 25:37.160
Says the King.

25:37.160 --> 25:41.160
But it can kiss my hand.

25:41.160 --> 25:43.160
No, thank you!

25:43.160 --> 25:45.160
Says the Cheshire Cat.

25:45.160 --> 25:48.160
The King is angry and calls the Queen.

25:48.160 --> 25:50.160
My dear.

25:50.160 --> 25:52.160
Take this cat away.

25:52.160 --> 25:54.160
Of course.

25:54.160 --> 25:55.160
Says the Queen.

25:55.160 --> 25:57.160
Cut off its head!

25:57.160 --> 26:00.160
Everyone looks at the Cheshire Cat.

26:00.160 --> 26:02.160
A soldier says.

26:02.160 --> 26:06.160
I can't cut off its head because it hasn't got a body.

26:06.160 --> 26:08.160
It's got a head.

26:08.160 --> 26:10.160
Says the King angrily.

26:10.160 --> 26:12.160
Cut it off.

26:12.160 --> 26:15.160
It's the Duchess's Cheshire Cat.

26:15.160 --> 26:16.160
Says Alice.

26:16.160 --> 26:18.160
Ask her.

26:18.160 --> 26:20.160
The Duchess is in prison.

26:20.160 --> 26:22.160
Bring her here.

26:22.160 --> 26:25.160
Says the Queen to a soldier.

26:25.160 --> 26:28.160
Suddenly, the Cheshire Cat goes away.

26:32.160 --> 26:35.160
Chapter 6. The Trial.

26:36.160 --> 26:39.160
Suddenly, someone shouts.

26:39.160 --> 26:41.160
The trail's beginning.

26:41.160 --> 26:43.160
The trail's beginning.

26:43.160 --> 26:44.160
A trail?

26:44.160 --> 26:46.160
asks Alice.

26:46.160 --> 26:48.160
Whose trail is it?

26:48.160 --> 26:50.160
But no one answers Alice.

26:50.160 --> 26:53.160
She is soon in the courtroom.

26:53.160 --> 26:57.160
The King and Queen of Hearts are sitting on their thrones.

26:57.160 --> 27:01.160
The nave of hearts is standing in front of them.

27:01.160 --> 27:06.160
There are a lot of birds, animals and cards sitting in the courtroom.

27:06.160 --> 27:10.160
In the middle, there is a table with a big plate of tarts on it.

27:10.160 --> 27:16.160
The white rabbit is near the King with a long piece of paper in his hand.

27:16.160 --> 27:18.160
He starts reading.

27:18.160 --> 27:25.160
The Queen of Hearts, she makes some tarts all on a summer day.

27:25.160 --> 27:30.160
But the nave of hearts, he takes the tarts away.

27:30.160 --> 27:32.160
Cut off his head!

27:32.160 --> 27:34.160
Shouts the Queen.

27:34.160 --> 27:35.160
Oh no!

27:35.160 --> 27:37.160
Says the white rabbit.

27:37.160 --> 27:40.160
We've got to listen to some witnesses first.

27:40.160 --> 27:42.160
Very well.

27:42.160 --> 27:43.160
Says the King.

27:43.160 --> 27:46.160
Call the first witness.

27:46.160 --> 27:49.160
The first witness is the Hatter.

27:49.160 --> 27:54.160
He has got a teacup in one hand and bread and butter in the other.

27:54.160 --> 27:58.160
I'm sorry about this, but it's my tea time.

27:58.160 --> 27:59.160
Says the Hatter.

27:59.160 --> 28:01.160
Oh really?

28:01.160 --> 28:03.160
Says the King.

28:03.160 --> 28:05.160
Take off your hat.

28:05.160 --> 28:07.160
It isn't mine.

28:07.160 --> 28:08.160
Says the Hatter.

28:08.160 --> 28:10.160
Whose hat is it then?

28:10.160 --> 28:12.160
Asks the King angrily.

28:12.160 --> 28:14.160
I don't know.

28:14.160 --> 28:16.160
Says the Hatter.

28:16.160 --> 28:18.160
I sell hats.

28:18.160 --> 28:20.160
Tell me what you know.

28:20.160 --> 28:21.160
Says the King.

28:21.160 --> 28:23.160
Oh, I don't know anything.

28:23.160 --> 28:25.160
Says the Hatter.

28:25.160 --> 28:28.160
The Queen looks at the Hatter with her glasses.

28:28.160 --> 28:32.160
He is afraid of her and his face is white.

28:32.160 --> 28:36.160
He bites a piece of his teacup instead of his bread and butter.

28:36.160 --> 28:39.160
I'm just a poor man.

28:39.160 --> 28:41.160
Says the Hatter sadly.

28:41.160 --> 28:45.160
Please let me go and finish my tea.

28:45.160 --> 28:46.160
Very well.

28:46.160 --> 28:47.160
You can go.

28:47.160 --> 28:49.160
Says the King.

28:49.160 --> 28:52.160
Can't off his head outside?

28:52.160 --> 28:54.160
The Queen says to one of the soldiers.

28:54.160 --> 28:59.160
But the Hatter runs away quickly and no one can catch him.

28:59.160 --> 29:02.160
Suddenly Alice feels strange.

29:02.160 --> 29:03.160
Oh no.

29:03.160 --> 29:07.160
She thinks I'm growing again.

29:07.160 --> 29:09.160
Call the next witness.

29:09.160 --> 29:11.160
Shouts the King.

29:11.160 --> 29:14.160
The next witness is the Duchess's cook.

29:14.160 --> 29:20.160
She comes into the courtroom with a big pepper pot and everyone sneezes.

29:20.160 --> 29:23.160
Tell me everything you know.

29:23.160 --> 29:24.160
Says the King.

29:24.160 --> 29:25.160
No.

29:25.160 --> 29:27.160
Says the cook.

29:27.160 --> 29:31.160
The King is surprised and looks at the white rabbit.

29:31.160 --> 29:35.160
Ask the witness questions your majesty.

29:35.160 --> 29:37.160
Says the white rabbit quietly.

29:37.160 --> 29:38.160
Oh.

29:38.160 --> 29:39.160
That's right.

29:39.160 --> 29:40.160
Says the King.

29:40.160 --> 29:44.160
What are tarts made of?

29:44.160 --> 29:48.160
The Maid of Pepper answers the cook.

29:48.160 --> 29:51.160
The Maid of Sugar.

29:51.160 --> 29:53.160
Says the Sleepy Door Mouse.

29:53.160 --> 29:54.160
What?

29:54.160 --> 29:55.160
Says the Queen.

29:55.160 --> 29:57.160
Send the door mouse away.

29:57.160 --> 29:59.160
Can't off its head.

29:59.160 --> 30:02.160
There is a lot of noise in the courtroom.

30:02.160 --> 30:05.160
And at last the door mouse goes away.

30:05.160 --> 30:08.160
Call the next witness.

30:08.160 --> 30:10.160
Says the King.

30:10.160 --> 30:15.160
The white rabbit looks at his long piece of paper and says...

30:15.160 --> 30:16.160
Alice.

30:16.160 --> 30:19.160
Alice is very surprised.

30:19.160 --> 30:21.160
She is quite big now.

30:21.160 --> 30:26.160
She stands up quickly and some of the birds and animals fall over.

30:26.160 --> 30:27.160
Oh.

30:27.160 --> 30:28.160
Says Alice.

30:28.160 --> 30:30.160
I'm very sorry.

30:30.160 --> 30:34.160
Then she goes and stands in front of the King and Queen.

30:34.160 --> 30:37.160
What do you know about this?

30:37.160 --> 30:38.160
Asks the King.

30:38.160 --> 30:41.160
Nothing answers Alice.

30:41.160 --> 30:44.160
That's very important.

30:44.160 --> 30:45.160
Says the King.

30:45.160 --> 30:48.160
You mean unimportant to your majesty.

30:48.160 --> 30:50.160
Says the white rabbit.

30:50.160 --> 30:51.160
Of course.

30:51.160 --> 30:52.160
Says the King.

30:52.160 --> 30:55.160
I mean unimportant.

30:55.160 --> 31:02.160
Then he writes something in a book.

31:02.160 --> 31:06.160
A Real Queen.

31:06.160 --> 31:12.160
Her name is Elizabeth Alexandra Mary Windsor.

31:12.160 --> 31:19.160
Her date of birth is the 21st of April 1926.

31:19.160 --> 31:26.160
She becomes Queen on the 27th of May 1952.

31:26.160 --> 31:31.160
Her title is Queen Elizabeth II.

31:31.160 --> 31:37.160
She is Queen of the United Kingdom of Great Britain and Northern Ireland.

31:37.160 --> 31:42.160
Her husband is Philip Duke of Edinburgh.

31:42.160 --> 31:51.160
She has got three sons, Charles, Andrew and Edward and one daughter, Anne.

31:51.160 --> 31:55.160
She has got eight grandchildren.

31:55.160 --> 32:01.160
She loves dogs, especially corgis.

32:01.160 --> 32:07.160
She loves horses and she loves horse riding.

32:07.160 --> 32:12.160
When she is in London, she lives in Buckingham Palace.

32:12.160 --> 32:20.160
Her other homes are Windsor Castle near London and Sandringham House in the east of England.

32:20.160 --> 32:25.160
She has got a castle in Scotland, Balmoral Castle.

32:25.160 --> 32:32.160
She goes here for her summer holidays.

32:32.160 --> 32:37.160
Chapter 7. Back home for tea.

32:37.160 --> 32:40.160
Silence in the courtroom.

32:40.160 --> 32:42.160
Shouts the King.

32:42.160 --> 32:46.160
I have got an important rule for you.

32:46.160 --> 32:49.160
Everyone is silent and looks at the King.

32:49.160 --> 32:52.160
He opens a book and reads.

32:52.160 --> 32:54.160
Rule 42.

32:54.160 --> 33:00.160
All people, more than a mile tall, must leave the courtroom.

33:00.160 --> 33:03.160
Everyone looks at Alice.

33:03.160 --> 33:05.160
I'm not a mile tall.

33:05.160 --> 33:06.160
Says Alice.

33:06.160 --> 33:08.160
Yes you are.

33:08.160 --> 33:09.160
Says the King.

33:09.160 --> 33:12.160
You're more than two miles tall.

33:12.160 --> 33:14.160
Says the Queen.

33:14.160 --> 33:16.160
I don't want to leave the courtroom.

33:16.160 --> 33:17.160
Says Alice.

33:17.160 --> 33:19.160
It's not a real rule.

33:19.160 --> 33:22.160
It's a very old rule.

33:22.160 --> 33:24.160
Says the King.

33:24.160 --> 33:29.160
Then why is it rule 42 and not rule one?

33:29.160 --> 33:31.160
Ask Alice.

33:31.160 --> 33:35.160
The King does not know what to say and closes the book quickly.

33:35.160 --> 33:38.160
The White Rabbit jumps up and says.

33:38.160 --> 33:41.160
Look, I've got a letter.

33:41.160 --> 33:44.160
He puts his glasses on and looks at it.

33:44.160 --> 33:47.160
Oh, it's not a letter.

33:47.160 --> 33:48.160
It's a poem.

33:48.160 --> 33:50.160
He says.

33:50.160 --> 33:55.160
Read it from the beginning and stop at the end.

33:55.160 --> 33:56.160
Says the King.

33:56.160 --> 34:01.160
The White Rabbit reads the poem, but no one understands it.

34:01.160 --> 34:03.160
This poem is nonsense.

34:03.160 --> 34:04.160
Says Alice.

34:04.160 --> 34:07.160
Oh, cut off the naves hit.

34:07.160 --> 34:09.160
Says the Queen.

34:09.160 --> 34:11.160
What nonsense?

34:11.160 --> 34:12.160
Shouts Alice.

34:12.160 --> 34:16.160
She is not afraid of anyone now because she is very big.

34:16.160 --> 34:18.160
Be quiet.

34:18.160 --> 34:19.160
Shouts the Queen.

34:19.160 --> 34:20.160
No.

34:20.160 --> 34:21.160
Shouts Alice.

34:21.160 --> 34:25.160
The Queen is very angry and her face is purple.

34:25.160 --> 34:28.160
Cut off her hand.

34:28.160 --> 34:29.160
She shouts.

34:29.160 --> 34:31.160
I'm not afraid of you.

34:31.160 --> 34:32.160
Says Alice.

34:32.160 --> 34:34.160
You're only cards.

34:34.160 --> 34:39.160
Suddenly the cards fly up into the air and fall down on her.

34:39.160 --> 34:41.160
Oh dear.

34:41.160 --> 34:42.160
Says Alice.

34:42.160 --> 34:45.160
She pushes the cards away from her face.

34:45.160 --> 34:47.160
Alice wakes up.

34:47.160 --> 34:49.160
These cards are leaves.

34:49.160 --> 34:52.160
Her sister pushes them away from her face.

34:52.160 --> 34:54.160
Wake up Alice dear.

34:54.160 --> 34:56.160
Says her sister.

34:56.160 --> 34:57.160
Oh.

34:57.160 --> 34:59.160
What a strange dream.

34:59.160 --> 35:01.160
Says Alice.

35:01.160 --> 35:03.160
Please tell me about it.

35:03.160 --> 35:05.160
Says her sister.

35:05.160 --> 35:08.160
Alice tells her sister about the dream.

35:08.160 --> 35:11.160
Her sister listens and then laughs.

35:11.160 --> 35:12.160
Haha.

35:12.160 --> 35:13.160
Yes.

35:13.160 --> 35:14.160
She says.

35:14.160 --> 35:16.160
It's a very strange dream.

35:16.160 --> 35:20.160
But it's late now and it's time for your tea.

35:21.160 --> 35:27.160
Alice runs home and thinks about the white rabbit, the caterpillar, the duchess, the

35:27.160 --> 35:34.160
hatter, the Cheshire cat, the croquet game, the queen, the king and the cards.

35:34.160 --> 35:37.160
What a wonderful dream.

35:37.160 --> 35:38.160
She says happily.

35:38.160 --> 35:43.160
One day I can tell my children about it.

